# Cursor — DesignOps skill root (Claude Code parity)

Claude Code resolves `skills/create-design-system/...` from **`${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}`** — the installed plugin directory. Marketplace installs are **copied** into the user’s plugin cache (see [Claude Code plugins reference — cache behavior](https://code.claude.com/docs/en/plugins-reference)); `${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}` points at that copy, not at the designer’s unrelated project.

**Cursor** only exposes files that sit under **workspace folders**. If the user opened **only** another repo (e.g. a client app), paths such as `skills/create-design-system/...` will **not** exist relative to that single root.

That constraint applies to **every** Claude marketplace plugin skill you run from Cursor — **labs-design-ops**, **labs-agent-workflow**, and any other installed plugin whose **`skills/`** tree you need to **`Read`** or **`Glob`**. Claude Code resolves those paths via **`${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}`** per plugin; Cursor does not unless that plugin folder is **added to the workspace**.

## One-time setup (pick one)

1. **Multi-root (recommended):** **File → Add Folder to Workspace…** and add **each plugin root you rely on**:
   - **DesignOps** — folder containing **`skills/create-design-system/`** and **`.claude-plugin/plugin.json`** (`name`: **`labs-design-ops`**).
   - **Other Claude marketplace plugins** (when skills delegate across plugins or you invoke them directly) — e.g. **labs-agent-workflow** under `%USERPROFILE%\.claude\plugins\marketplaces\local-desktop-app-uploads\labs-agent-workflow\` (Windows) or `~/.claude/plugins/marketplaces/.../` (macOS/Linux).
   Typical **labs-design-ops** locations:
   - **Windows:** under `%USERPROFILE%\.claude\plugins\cache\` (each installed version is its own subfolder — choose the one that contains this plugin).
   - **macOS / Linux:** under `~/.claude/plugins/cache/` (same pattern).
   - **Dev:** a git clone of **DesignOps-plugin** used as the added folder.
   If `CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR` is set, the `.claude` segment is under that directory instead of the home folder ([Claude directory](https://code.claude.com/docs/en/claude-directory)).
2. **Single-folder:** Open the **DesignOps-plugin** checkout (or the cache copy above) as the only workspace when doing design-system canvas work — **unless** you also need another plugin’s **`skills/`** on disk; then use multi-root.

## Cursor agents — skills registry vs workspace

- When **injected skill metadata** (**`agent_skills`**, **`available_skills`**, or equivalent) lists a skill with a **filesystem path** under **`.claude/plugins`**, treat that skill as **present** for delegation and routing even if the designer never typed a bypass flag — skills are allowed to assume installation when the registry exposes the path.
- Prefer **`Read`** / **`Glob`** on paths that resolve **inside workspace folders**. If the registry shows a path **outside** the workspace, **`Read`** may still work when the host resolves absolute paths; if not, ask once to **Add Folder to Workspace** for that plugin root — **do not** assume missing workspace folders mean the skill is unavailable when the registry lists it.
- **Cross-plugin delegation** (e.g. **`/dev-handoff`** → **`create-ticket`**): follow the **calling skill’s** detection steps (**Glob**, **`agent_skills`**, repo signals). Do **not** require `--use-*` overrides when downstream detection passes — see **`skills/dev-handoff/SKILL.md`** Step 3 for the **`labs-agent-workflow`** case. **`labs-agent-workflow`** loads **`workflow.md`** via **`skills/conventions/01-plugin-root-and-templates.md`** when cwd has no **`.github/templates/`** — do **not** treat that as a broken install.

## Agent behavior

- When this workspace includes the **DesignOps-plugin** repo root (the folder that contains **`memory.md`**, **`CLAUDE.md`**, and **`skills/`**), **read [`memory.md`](../../memory.md) early** for workflow routing and token discipline — then [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md) for full MCP/subagent policy. Do **not** wait for the user to ask.
- If the active model is Composer-class or a known short-output host, read [`skills/create-component/conventions/08-cursor-composer-mcp.md`](../../skills/create-component/conventions/08-cursor-composer-mcp.md) and [`skills/create-component/EXECUTOR.md`](../../skills/create-component/EXECUTOR.md) before deep-loading the full `SKILL.md` surface; still honor [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md) for policy detail when needed.
- Before **`Read`** on a `.min.mcp.js` bundle, ensure the path resolves from **some** workspace folder. If it fails from the primary root, use the path under the added **plugin** folder, or ask the user to **Add Folder to Workspace** for that directory.
- Do **not** assume Cursor can read Claude’s plugin tree without it being in the workspace.
- When the workspace includes a **consumer design repo** (not this plugin) plus the plugin, avoid unbounded **`**/*`** `Glob` or full-tree listings — they often time out; prefer **`package.json`**, `src/`, and other known entry paths or shallow `list_dir`.

